  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Integrated Services and Promotion of Social Cohesion through a Municipal Migrant and Refugee Centre in Izmir</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project seeks to support the Izmir metropolitan municipality in implementing a model for integrated service delivery to migrants, refugees and other vulnerable groups to promote social cohesion with the host community.  The project will ensure that establishment of a municipality centre for migrants and refugees will provide counselling and referral services as well as support the existing municipality services through financial and in-kind support to include migrant and refugee groups in their actions. The project will also seek to strengthen the capacity of relevant stakeholders including the municipality, local public institutions, and NGOs in working with and for migrants, refugees and the host community through comprehensive technical assistance and capacity building actions. The project will enhance consultation and communication channels between migrants, refugees and host communities in order to enhance dialogue and social cohesion in selected municipalities and in particular aiming to reduce inter-communal tensions that may arise from real and perceived competition for employment, resources and access to public services. Together these components will ensure that the Izmir municipality has the framework in place to sustainably operate its services tailored for migrants and refugees.</narrative>
  </description>
